About this web application
This application aims to provide support as a communication aide based on the experience of before, during and after visiting healthcare facilities. This application has a list of hospitals in Nonoichi city, symptoms and personal information, appointment procedure, comments from the doctor, and medicine information. 
This web application was designed and developed to support visits to healthcare facilities for foreign residents by Ryusei Nomi and Akari Kikuda for their 2015 senior-year project at Kanazawa Technical College, under the initiative of KTC COTech (Community-Oriented Technology) lab. COTech seeks to solve local and social issues using ICT, and was proposed by Omihiti Matsushita and Robert Songer, faculty of Kanazawa Technical College.

DISCLAIMER

This application is provided as is under the assumption that any and all users understand the inherent risks involved in relying on a web application for the intercultural communication of sensitive information related to personal health.
